Please take time folks, to study our auction photograph closely as they along with our detailed written listing will best describe this fantastic vintage collectable revolver. This is one of the early, and more desirable, pinned and recessed models. The factory fitted 3 ½ inch barrel is designed with a full length factory rib, or sight plain. The top of the barrel rib, along with the top of the frame, and the click adjustable rear sight all have a factory checkered pattern, or cross hatch pattern style finish, designed to cut down on glare from light when shooting. This designed feature is only found on the S&W Model 27 revolvers. The 3 1/2 inch barrel along with the six round cylinder chambers all have perfect bores, are chambered for the famous 357 Magnum cartridges, however this revolver will also chamber the .38 S&W Special cartridges, which are the same diameter, are interchangeable with the .357 Mag. cartridges, and are less expensive, with reduced felt recoil for more enjoyable target shooting. This beautifully designed revolver is factory fitted with the following options, a stationary quick draw serrated ramp style front sight, a fully adjustable square notch micrometer click rear sight, standard trigger, semi-wide target style hammer, and a very nice pair of S&W medallion Magna style Checkered Grips original to the revolver and correctly numbered to it. The grips have remained in great condition over the years, have nice sharp checkering, and have no chips, cracks, or flaws. This revolver is almost like new, still functions perfectly, has a nice smooth action, with a nice crisp trigger pull, and the factory applied case colors on the target style hammer and trigger are vibrant. This beauty has been amazingly well preserved over the past 48 years. The perfect fit and finish of the metal parts, along with the over-all factory original condition of this beautiful vintage Smith & Wesson Model 27-2 Revolver, would be near impossible to upgrade. To complete this very nice vintage package the revolver is still housed in the original Smith & Wesson two piece solid Silver border two piece blue box with correct matching end label still attached matching this guns specifics and serial number exactly, and the box has no exterior damage or repairs. This beautiful vintage revolver was found by the owners family in the rear of his gun vault, still wrapped in the factory supplied wax paper wrapping, and still housed in the factory shipping box as shown. There is no doubt that this beauty was well kept & maintained over the years by it's owner, which certainly helped to protect, and preserve it, and certainly adds to the over-all quality, and value of the revolver today. This is definitely one of the nicest packages you could ever find, and would be very difficult to upgrade. Also included inside the box are the original S&W factory shipping documents as shown in our auction photographs, including a Parts list, and the factory original cleaning kit, which consists of an aluminum cleaning rod, cotton bore swab, bore brush, and sight adjustment tool. What a fantastic vintage S&W Model 27-2 revolver, and if you are the winning bidder you will get it all, just like it was shipped from the factory 48 years ago. Most collectors and shooters alike will look far and wide to find another package that even comes close in comparison. This would be an excellent addition to even the most advanced collections, and also would make a fine investment. This is simply an absolutely great revolver! postcontent: FREE SHIPPING by buying direct at (www.partsofwar.com)The FERFRANS CQB Modular Muzzle Brake System is a two part system consisting of the performance muzzle brake mount + CRD (Concussion Reduction Device) which features a built in quick attach/detach mechanism. The muzzle brake effectively mitigates felt recoil and muzzle movement and with the CRD attached does this while minimizing side blast/concussion and redirects sound to the front of the shooter. It is a two piece modular system that includes (1) very effective high performance muzzle brake and (2) a ported Concussion Reduction Device (CRD) that attaches to the muzzle brake using a quick detach mechanism. The CRD has strategically placed side ports that allow the muzzle brake to retain its compensator functionality as opposed to brake shields that cover the brake and negates its function. With the CRD attached, recoil feels like a slight, straight to the rear push (it's a softer recoil feel, not the typical sharp kick). It is, of course, a compromise between reducing side concussion versus minimizing felt recoil. We believe we have achieved an optimal balance of sufficient brake/ compensator functionality (muzzle leveling effect) and side concussion reduction. The CRD has a quick detach/attach mechanism to allow you to easily switch back to a full brake whenever you.
